The paper discusses a semantic foundation for multi-tier programming languages, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). It also deals with location information and type-directed slicing compilations, which are related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also formulates a type system and discusses semantic correctness, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
